      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Basicity / cationic fraction at pH 7.4\n- Many high-risk hERG blockers have a **readily protonated tertiary amine** (pKa often ~8\u201310), giving a dominant **cationic species** that engages the channel (notably **cation\u2013\u03c0** interactions).\n- Here, the most plausible \u201cbasic center\u201d is the **imine-like N in the 5-member ring**, which is typically **moderately/basic-to-weakly basic** (often lower pKa than dialkylamines).  \n  \u2192 **Lower fraction protonated** at physiological pH generally **reduces hERG risk**.\n- The **pyridine N-oxide** is **not** a typical protonatable/basic nitrogen and increases polarity.",
