      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Polarity / desolvation penalty\n- The **N-oxide + alcohol + multiple ethers** increase **PSA** and H-bonding capacity.\n- Increased polarity can impose a **desolvation penalty** for deep binding in the hydrophobic hERG cavity, often **reducing affinity** versus classic cationic lipophiles.",
